cess\n\nC-Link's Terrestrial Storage utilizes MicroSnap's carbon preservation technology—an advanced microbial process that stabilizes organic carbon at ambient temperature through controlled biological activity.\n\n### Verified Performance Metrics:\n\n__Energy efficiency__\n\nProduces biochar-equivalent carbon storage using approximately one-tenth the energy of thermal pyrolysis\n\n__Mass retention__\n\nPreserves 95-97% of starting material mass, maximizing both carbon capture and product yield\n\n__Processing time__\n\nCompletes stabilization in 14-60 days versus 6-12 months for traditional composting\n\n__Storage stability__\n\nIndependently verified to 100-year permanence standards\n\nSafety Advantages: Ambient-temperature processing eliminates fire risks inherent in thermal composting and pyrolysis operations. This reduces insurance costs and enables deployment in urban and suburban contexts where thermal operations face regulatory barriers.\n\nPathogen and Contaminant Elimination: Third-party testing confirms complete destruction of pathogens including fecal coliforms and salmonella. Recent testing demonstrates elimination of PFAS (per- and polyfluoroalkyl substances) to below detection limits—addressing one of the most persistent environmental contaminants in biosolids and municipal waste streams.\n\n## Carbon Removal Verification\n\nC-Link CORCs undergo independent third-party verification evaluating:\n\nFeedstock sourcing and baseline emissions\n\nProcess lifecycle emissions and energy inputs\n\nCarbon storage stability and permanence\n\nAdditionality and double-counting prevention\n\nCertificates are validated on Puro.earth , which has been approved by the Integrity Council for the Voluntary Carbon Market (ICVCM) as an Eligible Carbon Crediting Programme, meeting institutional buyer requirements for transparency, traceability, and compliance with emerging carbon accounting standards.\n\nCORC Differentiation: Carbon removal certificates represent physical CO2 extracted from the atmosphere and stored long-term, distinct from avoidance-style offsets that prevent future emissions. This distinction matters increasingly as regulatory frameworks and corporate climate commitments require demonstrated removals rather than avoided emissions.10:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"min-h-screen bg-[color:var(--color-cream)] pt-28 pb-24\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mb-16\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-[color:var(--color-gold)] text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase mb-4\",\"children\":\"Active Projects\"}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"className\":\"font-serif text-5xl sm:text-6xl text-[color:var(--color-indigo)] mb-6\",\"children\":\"Companies we believe in\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"max-w-2xl text-lg text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed\",\"children\":\"We partner with founders who are building measurable solutions to to the most challenging humanity and planetary problems — we believe that smart people who care can change the world\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"$L19\",null,{\"companies\":[{\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[],\"concepts\":[]},\"sys\":{\"space\":{\"sys\":{\"type\":\"Link\",\"linkType\":\"Space\",\"id\":\"lp5y22r82q1h\"}},\"id\":\"7wznFnBg50okAGMnSPziSO\",\"type\":\"Entry\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-01T08:02:34.900Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-03-01T08:19:00.623Z\",\"environment\":{\"sys\":{\"id\":\"master\",\"type\":\"Link\",\"linkType\":\"Environment\"}},\"publishedVersion\":25,\"revision\":2,\"contentType\":{\"sys\":{\"type\":\"Link\",\"linkType\":\"ContentType\",\"id\":\"portfolioCompany\"}},\"locale\":\"en-US\"},\"fields\":{\"name\":\"C-link\",\"slug\":\"c-link\",\"logo\":{\"metadata\":{\"tags\":[],\"concepts\":[]},\"sys\":{\"space\":{\"sys\":{\"type\":\"Link\",\"linkType\":\"Space\",\"id\":\"lp5y22r82q1h\"}},\"id\":\"1XmbNSAHGe8wxM7fJsA9Ua\",\"type\":\"Asset\",\"created